==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unguis
<hw>Un"guis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Ungues</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., nail, claw, or
hoof.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The nail, claw, talon, or hoof of a
finger, toe, or other appendage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the terminal hooks on the
foot of an insect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The slender base of a petal in
some flowers; a claw; called also <altname>ungula</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ungula</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
